Lexington Avenue, north from East 29th Street. On the left, at 30th Street appears the First Moravian Church (founded 1746) and the N. Y. School of Design for Women.
April 13, 1924
Standard Photographic Service
Gift of Borough President of Manhattan

Lexington Avenue at N. W. corner of 29th Street.
February 23, 1931.
P.L. Sperr,Photographer.
The New York
PUBLIC LIBRARY

131 to 135 East 29th Street (left to right), adioining and east of the N.E. corner of Lexington Ave., showing the Congregation Adereth El at No. 135. The adjoining structure No. 133 is used in conjunction with same and is the Talmud Torah Adereth El. No. 131, which appears on the left is occupied by the International Federation of Catholic Alumnae, Business and Bulletin Headquarters.
September 1937.
George D. Chinn.
